<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-09-06T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-09-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="723" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d723">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">823.00/300: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-09-06T14:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            6, 1919, 2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received September 7, 7.44 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>During the last few days Belgium, Bolivia, Ecuador, France and Italy
                                have recognized the Peruvian Government. Uruguay and England have
                                recognized the <hi rend="italic">de facto</hi> Government.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>